n = int(input())
def divisor(n):
    divs = [1]
    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5)+1):
        if n % i == 0:
            divs.append(i)
            if i != n // i:
                divs.append(n//i)
    return divs

ans = 1
for i in range(2,n+1):
    divs = divisor(i)
    ans *= len(divs)+1
    ans %= 10**9+7
print(ans)

import sys

def min_max(arr):
    min_val = sys.maxsize
    max_val = -sys.maxsize

    for i in range(len(arr)):
        if arr[i] < min_val:
            min_val = arr[i]
        if arr[i] > max_val:
            max_val = arr[i]
    return min_val, max_val

arr = [int(x) for x in input().split()]

min_val, max_val = min_max(arr)

print(min_val, max_val)
